 <sect1 xml:id="sec-gnome-gconf-templates">
  <title>Adding Document Templates</title>

  <para>
   To add document templates for users, fill in the
   <filename>Templates</filename> directory in a user's home directory. You
   can do this manually for each user by copying the files into
   <filename>~/Templates</filename>, or system-wide by adding a
   <filename>Templates</filename> directory with documents to
   <filename>/etc/skel</filename> before the user is created.
  </para>

  <para>
   A user creates a new document from a template by right-clicking the
   desktop and selecting <guimenu>Create Document</guimenu>.
  </para>
 </sect1>
